of a group of middle-class women in Tokyo who participated in a weekly support meeting for families of substance abusers at a public mental-health clinic. Amy Borovoy deftly analyzes the dilemmas of being female in modern Japan and the grace with which women struggle within a system that supports wives and mothers but thwarts their attempts to find fulfillment outside the family. The central concerns of the book reach beyond the problem of alcoholism to examine the women's own processes of self-reflection and criticism and the deeper fissures and asymmetries that undergird Japanese productivity and social order.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAlcoholicsxFamily relationshipsxJapanxTokyo. 0aAlcoholicsxFamily relationshipszJapanzTokyo. 0aAlcoholics' spousesxJapanxTokyo. 0aAlcoholics' spouseszJapanzTokyo. 0aCodependencyxJapanxTokyo. 0aCodependencyzJapanzTokyo. 0aParents of drug addictsxJapanxTokyo. 0aParents of drug addictszJapanzTokyo. 0aSex rolexJapanxTokyo. 0aSex rolezJapanzTokyo. 0aSocial work with womenxJapanxTokyo. 0aSocial work with womenzJapanzTokyo. 0aWivesxJapanxTokyo. 0aWiveszJapanzTokyo. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938687423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520938687.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles